{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01T6LpQ4PSBzSiLM6QB2ZQ6q","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→artifact: spec\n     3→loop: 2\n     4→project: ralph-burning-rewrite\n     5→backend: codex(gpt-5.4-xhigh)\n     6→role: planner\n     7→created_at: 2026-03-11T18:33:24Z\n     8→---\n     9→\n    10→I’m reviewing `prompt.md`, the completed loop artifact, and recent git history to determine what’s already in place and what the next missing feature slice should be.\n    11→I have the loop and commit boundaries. Next I’m reading the actual prompt/spec inputs and the rewrite code so I can separate shipped foundation work from the next missing slice.\n    12→The prompt lives under the existing orchestration workspace, not the rewrite tree. I’m pulling the project prompt plus loop spec and current implementation surface together now.\n    13→The checked-in crate is still a narrow foundation slice. I’m reading the workflow and workspace modules now to verify whether stage contracts, effective config, or any project/run persistence already slipped in before I plan the next feature.\n    14→I’ve confirmed the current code matches the approved loop-1 foundation plus a later `flake.nix` addition. I’m checking the checkpoint diffs now so the next feature is anchored to what actually changed between planning, implementation, review, and current HEAD.\n    15→# Feature: Stage Contract Registry and Deterministic Artifact Rendering\n    16→\n    17→## Description\n    18→Loop 1 is complete: the approved artifact and git checkpoints `1dbe79b` through `60e6d0c` delivered the Rust crate skeleton, bounded-context module layout, workspace init, built-in flow discovery, and the shared `FlowPreset` / `StageId` foundation. The only later change at `cac0f25` adds `flake.nix` support and does not add workflow behavior. The next missing slice is the unfinished remainder of roadmap step 2: a `StageContract` and renderer layer for the already-defined stages. The current codebase has no stage payload schemas, no semantic validators, no failure-class mapping, and no deterministic Markdown artifact rendering, so later work on agent execution and `run start` would otherwise have no canonical contract to target.\n    19→\n    20→## Acceptance Criteria\n    21→- [ ] Add a `StageContract` registry keyed by the existing `StageId`, and every stage already present in the four built-in presets resolves to exactly one contract without changing any approved flow IDs or stage ordering.\n    22→- [ ] Introduce typed stage payload models plus JSON Schema generation/validation for all supported stages: `prompt_review`, `planning`, `implementation`, `qa`, `review`, `completion_panel`, `acceptance_qa`, `final_review`, `plan_and_implement`, `apply_fixes`, `docs_plan`, `docs_update`, `docs_validation`, `ci_plan`, `ci_update`, and `ci_validation`.\n    23→- [ ] Planning-style contracts (`prompt_review`, `planning`, `docs_plan`, `ci_plan`) require structured problem framing, assumptions or open questions, ordered proposed work, and explicit readiness or risk fields.\n    24→- [ ] Execution/update contracts (`implementation`, `plan_and_implement`, `apply_fixes`, `docs_update`, `ci_update`) require structured change summaries, intended or completed steps, validation evidence or plans, and outstanding-risk fields.\n    25→- [ ] Validation/review contracts (`qa`, `docs_validation`, `ci_validation`, `acceptance_qa`, `review`, `final_review`, `completion_panel`) require an explicit outcome/decision enum plus evidence, findings or gaps, and follow-up or amendment data when the outcome is not cleanly approved.\n    26→- [ ] Contract evaluation order is fixed: schema validation runs first, semantic validation runs only on schema-valid payloads, and rendering runs only on payloads that passed both prior steps.\n    27→- [ ] Introduce the canonical failure-class enum needed by later slices, including `transport_failure`, `schema_validation_failure`, `domain_validation_failure`, `timeout`, `cancellation`, and `qa_review_outcome_failure`.\n    28→- [ ] Stage contracts map non-passing QA/review/completion decisions to `qa_review_outcome_failure` without treating them as schema or domain failures.\n    29→- [ ] State invariants for this slice are explicit: on schema failure, semantic validation and rendering do not run; on domain failure, rendering does not run; on any failure, no success bundle is returned; callers receive either `validated payload + rendered artifact` together or an error, never one without the other.\n    30→- [ ] Markdown renderers are deterministic and stage-specific: the same validated payload always renders byte-identical output, uses canonical `cycle` terminology, and is derived only from validated structured fields rather than raw backend text.\n    31→- [ ] Raw backend output remains diagnostic-only input to the contract evaluator and is kept separate from payload and artifact outputs so later persistence work can store diagnostics without using Markdown as protocol.\n    32→- [ ] Add unit tests proving every stage in every built-in flow has contract coverage, schema failures short-circuit semantic validation, semantic failures short-circuit rendering, and repeated renders of the same payload are identical.\n    33→- [ ] Add conformance scenario IDs for successful contract evaluation, schema failure, domain failure, and QA/review outcome failure so later `run start` work inherits fixed public expectations.\n    34→- [ ] `cargo test` and `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` pass after the contract and renderer modules are added.\n    35→\n    36→## Files to Modify/Create\n    37→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/Cargo.toml` - add schema/validation dependencies needed for typed JSON Schema support\n    38→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs` - add shared failure-class and artifact/contract identity types used across contracts\n    39→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs` - add explicit schema-validation, domain-validation, and renderer error variants\n    40→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs` - expose the stage-contract registry alongside the existing flow definitions\n    41→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs` - define `StageContract`, registry lookup, contract evaluation ordering, and failure mapping\n    42→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/payloads.rs` - define typed payload structs and schema metadata for each stage or contract family\n    43→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/renderers.rs` - implement deterministic Markdown renderers from validated payloads\n    44→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit.rs` - register new unit test modules\n    45→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/stage_contract_test.rs` - cover registry completeness, validation ordering, and failure-class behavior\n    46→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/renderer_test.rs` - cover deterministic rendering and artifact content shape\n    47→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/stage_contracts.feature` - add scenario IDs describing contract success and failure behavior\n    48→\n    49→## Dependencies\n    50→- Requires: Loop 1 foundation — domain model, workspace init, and flow discovery\n    51→- Blocks: agent execution facade with structured-output guarantee, standard preset `run start` vertical path, and later retry/remediation semantics\n    52→\n    53→---\n    54→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Gx1iRbRieStJESk4vaaNVA","session_id":"68f65612-956d-4383-9b3f-2ff2c684a050","uuid":"686fa441-93d9-4374-aae1-08b66463e14c"}
