{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NeC94Er9PEvBv5oMSoKfti","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→artifact: spec\n     3→loop: 3\n     4→project: ralph-burning-rewrite\n     5→backend: claude(opus)\n     6→role: planner\n     7→created_at: 2026-03-11T19:11:51Z\n     8→---\n     9→\n    10→Now I have a complete picture of the project state. Let me analyze and produce the next feature spec.\n    11→\n    12→**Completed:**\n    13→- Loop 1 (roadmap slice 1): Foundation — domain model, workspace init, flow discovery\n    14→- Loop 2 (roadmap slice 2): Stage contract registry and deterministic artifact rendering\n    15→\n    16→**Next in roadmap:** Slice 3 — Workspace governance effective config + active project resolution\n    17→\n    18→# Feature: Workspace Governance Effective Config and Active Project Resolution\n    19→\n    20→## Description\n    21→Implement roadmap slice 3: layered workspace configuration with `config show/get/set/edit` CLI commands, and active-project resolution via the `.ralph-burning/active-project` pointer file. The existing `workspace_governance` context currently handles workspace init and config loading but has no support for effective configuration (workspace-level defaults, runtime overrides), mutable config updates, or tracking which project is currently selected. This slice fills that gap so that downstream work (project/run canonical store in slice 4, agent execution in slice 5) can resolve effective settings and know which project commands target without explicit `--id` flags.\n    22→\n    23→The config surface covers keys implied by the master prompt: `prompt_review.enabled` (controls whether the optional `prompt_review` stage runs in the `standard` flow), default backend family, default model overrides, and validation strictness. The implementation stores configuration in `workspace.toml` using a structured TOML schema, resolves effective values through a defaults-then-override chain, and enforces fail-fast on unsupported workspace versions (invariant already partially present, now wired through all config-reading paths).\n    24→\n    25→## Acceptance Criteria\n    26→- [ ] `workspace.toml` schema is extended with an optional `[settings]` table supporting at minimum these keys: `prompt_review.enabled` (bool, default `true`), `default_flow` (string, must be a valid `FlowPreset`, default `\"standard\"`), `default_backend` (string, optional), `default_model` (string, optional). Unknown keys in `[settings]` are preserved on round-trip (forward-compatible editing).\n    27→- [ ] An `EffectiveConfig` struct in `workspace_governance` resolves the full configuration by merging persisted `workspace.toml` settings with compiled defaults. Every supported key has a typed accessor with a documented default value. `EffectiveConfig::load(base_dir)` is the single entry point for all config reads.\n    28→- [ ] `ralph-burning config show` loads the workspace, checks the version (fail-fast on mismatch), and prints all effective settings as a human-readable TOML-like table showing each key, its effective value, and its source (`default` or `workspace.toml`).\n    29→- [ ] `ralph-burning config get <key>` prints the effective value for a single key. Exits non-zero with a clear error for unknown keys.\n    30→- [ ] `ralph-burning config set <key> <value>` validates the key name and value type, writes the updated value into `workspace.toml` under `[settings]`, and prints a confirmation. Exits non-zero for invalid keys or values (e.g., setting `default_flow` to an unknown preset).\n    31→- [ ] `ralph-burning config edit` opens `workspace.toml` in `$EDITOR` (or `$VISUAL`, falling back to `vi`). After the editor exits, the file is re-validated; if validation fails, the user is warned on stderr and the command exits non-zero (but the file is not reverted — the user must fix manually).\n    32→- [ ] `active-project` is a plain-text file in `.ralph-burning/` containing a single project ID (trimmed, no newline normalization issues). When absent, commands that require an active project fail with an explicit message naming `project select`.\n    33→- [ ] `ralph-burning project select <id>` validates that the project directory `.ralph-burning/projects/<id>/` exists and contains `project.toml`, writes the ID to `active-project`, and prints a confirmation. Exits non-zero if the project does not exist.\n    34→- [ ] A `resolve_active_project(base_dir) -> AppResult<ProjectId>` function in `workspace_governance` reads and validates `active-project`, returning a typed `ProjectId` or a descriptive error. This function is the single resolution point for all commands that operate on the current project.\n    35→- [ ] All config and active-project commands check workspace version first and fail fast on unsupported versions (wiring the existing `ensure_supported_workspace_version` through the CLI path).\n    36→- [ ] The filesystem adapter (`adapters/fs.rs`) gains methods for atomic config writes (write-to-temp-then-rename) and active-project file read/write, keeping side effects behind the adapter boundary.\n    37→- [ ] Unit tests cover: `EffectiveConfig` default resolution, override merging, round-trip serialization of extended `workspace.toml`, unknown-key preservation, invalid key/value rejection, active-project read/write/missing cases.\n    38→- [ ] Integration tests cover: `config show` output format, `config get` known and unknown keys, `config set` valid and invalid mutations, `project select` with existing and non-existing project directories.\n    39→- [ ] Gherkin scenarios added to `tests/conformance/features/workspace_config.feature`: show effective config, get known key, get unknown key, set valid key, set invalid value, set invalid key, edit with valid result, edit with invalid result.\n    40→- [ ] Gherkin scenarios added to `tests/conformance/features/active_project.feature`: select existing project, select non-existing project, resolve when no active project set, resolve after valid select.\n    41→- [ ] `cargo test` and `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` pass after all changes.\n    42→\n    43→## Files to Modify/Create\n    44→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs` — extend `WorkspaceConfig` with optional `settings: WorkspaceSettings` field; add `WorkspaceSettings` struct with typed config fields and defaults\n    45→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs` — add error variants: `UnknownConfigKey`, `InvalidConfigValue`, `NoActiveProject`, `ProjectNotFound`, `EditorFailed`\n    46→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/mod.rs` — add `EffectiveConfig` struct with `load()`, `get()`, `set()` methods; add `resolve_active_project()` and `set_active_project()` functions; refactor config loading to use extended schema\n    47→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/config.rs` — (new) effective config resolution logic, key registry, default values, validation of key names and value types\n    48→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs` — add `write_atomic()`, `read_active_project()`, `write_active_project()`, `open_editor()` methods\n    49→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/config.rs` — implement `show`, `get`, `set`, `edit` handlers replacing the current stubs\n    50→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/project.rs` — implement `select` handler (other project subcommands remain stubs)\n    51→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/config_test.rs` — unit tests for effective config resolution, merging, serialization, key validation\n    52→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/active_project_test.rs` — unit tests for active-project read/write/missing\n    53→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/workspace_config.feature` — Gherkin scenarios for config commands\n    54→- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/active_project.feature` — Gherkin scenarios for active project resolution\n    55→\n    56→## Dependencies\n    57→- Requires: Loop 1 (workspace init, `WorkspaceConfig`, filesystem adapter) and Loop 2 (flow preset validation for `default_flow` config key)\n    58→- Blocks: Slice 4 (project/run canonical store needs `resolve_active_project` and effective config), Slice 5 (agent execution needs default backend/model config resolution), Slice 6 (`run start` needs active project and effective config for prompt_review gate)\n    59→\n    60→---\n    61→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Gx1iRbRieStJESk4vaaNVA","session_id":"68f65612-956d-4383-9b3f-2ff2c684a050","uuid":"09d11957-bc4b-4d24-b630-397b5e9dcbde"}
