{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Gx1iRbRieStJESk4vaaNVA","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive summary.\n\n## Summary: Ralph-Burning Rewrite Project Status\n\nBased on my review of all four loop specifications and the current source code, here's what has been completed and what exists in the codebase:\n\n### Loop 1: Foundation — Domain Model, Workspace Init, and Flow Discovery\n**Status:** COMPLETED  \n**Scope:**\n- Bootstrap the `ralph-burning` Rust binary crate with foundation infrastructure\n- Implement workspace initialization command (`ralph-burning init`)\n- Implement flow discovery commands (`flow list` and `flow show`)\n- Define core domain types: `FlowPreset`, `StageId`, `StageCursor`, etc.\n- Create bounded-context folder skeleton\n\n**What was implemented:**\n- `Cargo.toml` with dependencies (clap, serde, toml, thiserror, chrono, tokio)\n- `/src/shared/domain.rs` with domain types (FlowPreset enum with Standard, QuickDev, DocsChange, CiImprovement)\n- Four built-in flow presets defined with their exact stage sequences\n- `FailureClass` enum for stage contract evaluation\n- Workspace initialization that creates `.ralph-burning/` directory with required subdirectories\n- Flow query functionality (list and show presets with descriptions and stage sequences)\n- Complete bounded-context skeleton: `workspace_governance`, `project_run_record`, `workflow_composition`, `agent_execution`, `requirements_drafting`, `automation_runtime`, `conformance_spec`, `adapters`, `shared`\n\n---\n\n### Loop 2: Stage Contract Registry and Deterministic Artifact Rendering\n**Status:** COMPLETED  \n**Scope:**\n- Add a `StageContract` registry keyed by `StageId`\n- Implement typed stage payload models with JSON Schema validation\n- Create failure-class mapping\n- Build deterministic Markdown artifact renderers\n\n**What was implemented:**\n- `/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs` - Stage contract registry and evaluation framework\n- `/src/contexts/workflow_composition/payloads.rs` - Typed payload structs for all 15 stage types:\n  - Planning-style: `prompt_review`, `planning`, `docs_plan`, `ci_plan`\n  - Execution/update: `implementation`, `plan_and_implement`, `apply_fixes`, `docs_update`, `ci_update`\n  - Validation/review: `qa`, `docs_validation`, `ci_validation`, `acceptance_qa`, `review`, `final_review`, `completion_panel`\n- `/src/contexts/workflow_composition/renderers.rs` - Deterministic Markdown renderers\n- Contract evaluation ordering: schema validation → semantic validation → rendering\n- Raw backend output kept separate from structured payload and artifacts (diagnostic-only)\n\n---\n\n### Loop 3: Workspace Governance Effective Config and Active Project Resolution\n**Status:** COMPLETED  \n**Scope:**\n- Implement layered workspace configuration with `config show/get/set/edit` commands\n- Implement active-project resolution via `.ralph-burning/active-project` pointer file\n- Add mutable config updates to workspace.toml\n\n**What was implemented:**\n- `/src/contexts/workspace_governance/config.rs` - `EffectiveConfig` struct with:\n  - `config show` - displays all effective settings with sources\n  - `config get <key>` - prints single key value\n  - `config set <key> <value>` - validates and updates workspace.toml\n  - `config edit` - opens workspace.toml in $EDITOR with validation\n- Config keys supported: `prompt_review.enabled`, `default_flow`, `default_backend`, `default_model`\n- `/src/contexts/workspace_governance/mod.rs` - workspace config management with:\n  - `resolve_active_project()` - reads and validates active-project file\n  - `load_workspace_config()` - loads configuration with version checking\n  - `ensure_supported_workspace_version()` - fail-fast on unsupported versions\n- `/src/cli/config.rs` and `/src/cli/project.rs` (select subcommand) - CLI handlers\n- Atomic config writes (write-to-temp-then-rename)\n\n---\n\n### Loop 4: Project and Run Record Foundation\n**Status:** COMPLETED  \n**Scope:**\n- Make `project_run_record` the durable source of truth\n- Implement canonical project storage with CRUD operations\n- Initialize run/journal state\n- Implement read-only run query commands (status, history, tail)\n\n**What was implemented:**\n- `/src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs` (241 lines) - Project and run domain models:\n  - `ProjectRecord` - immutable project metadata (id, name, flow, prompt hash, creation timestamp)\n  - `RunSnapshot` - canonical run state (active run pointer, status, stage cursor, cycle history, completion rounds, rollback metadata)\n  - `JournalEntry` - append-only journal events\n  - `PayloadRecord` and `ArtifactRecord` - durable history with strict separation from runtime logs\n  - `RuntimeLogEntry` - separate runtime-log records\n- `/src/contexts/project_run_record/journal.rs` (91 lines) - Append-only journal with sequence validation\n- `/src/contexts/project_run_record/queries.rs` (132 lines) - Read models for status, history, and tail with durable-history-only semantics\n- `/src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs` (329 lines) - Service layer with:\n  - `create_project` - atomic project creation with validation\n  - `list_projects` - canonical project enumeration\n  - `show_project` - project detail lookup\n  - `delete_project` - deletion with active-run checks\n  - `run_status`, `run_history`, `run_tail` - run query operations\n  - Port definitions: `ProjectStorePort`, `JournalStorePort`, `ArtifactStorePort`, `RuntimeLogStorePort`, `RunSnapshotPort`, `ActiveProjectPort`\n- `/src/cli/project.rs` and `/src/cli/run.rs` - CLI command handlers\n- `/src/adapters/fs.rs` - Filesystem adapter with atomic writes, NDJSON append helpers, prompt hashing\n- Atomic project staging with fail-fast on corruption\n- Strict separation of durable history (journal + payloads/artifacts) from runtime logs\n- Flow immutability enforced: cannot change flow after project creation\n\n---\n\n### Current Source Code Structure\n\n```\nralph-burning-rewrite/src/\n├── main.rs                  (async entry point, tracing init)\n├── lib.rs                   (public module re-exports)\n├── cli/\n│   ├── mod.rs              (top-level clap CLI dispatch)\n│   ├── init.rs             (ralph-burning init command)\n│   ├── flow.rs             (flow list/show commands)\n│   ├── config.rs           (config show/get/set/edit commands)\n│   ├── project.rs          (project create/list/show/delete/select commands)\n│   ├── run.rs              (run status/history/tail commands)\n│   ├── requirements.rs     (placeholder stub)\n│   ├── daemon.rs           (placeholder stub)\n│   └── conformance.rs      (placeholder stub)\n├── shared/\n│   ├── mod.rs              (shared module root)\n│   ├── domain.rs           (FlowPreset, StageId, FailureClass, ProjectId, RunId, etc.)\n│   └── error.rs            (shared error types)\n├── contexts/\n│   ├── mod.rs\n│   ├── workspace_governance/\n│   │   ├── mod.rs          (workspace init, config loading, version checking)\n│   │   └── config.rs       (EffectiveConfig with layered config resolution)\n│   ├── workflow_composition/\n│   │   ├── mod.rs          (flow preset registry and definitions)\n│   │   ├── contracts.rs    (StageContract registry and evaluation)\n│   │   ├── payloads.rs     (typed payload structs for all 15 stages)\n│   │   └── renderers.rs    (deterministic Markdown renderers)\n│   ├── project_run_record/\n│   │   ├── mod.rs          (context interface and port re-exports)\n│   │   ├── model.rs        (ProjectRecord, RunSnapshot, JournalEntry, etc.)\n│   │   ├── journal.rs      (append-only journal operations)\n│   │   ├── queries.rs      (read models: status, history, tail)\n│   │   └── service.rs      (CRUD use cases with port boundaries)\n│   ├── agent_execution/\n│   │   └── mod.rs          (stub)\n│   ├── requirements_drafting/\n│   │   └── mod.rs          (stub)\n│   ├── automation_runtime/\n│   │   └── mod.rs          (stub)\n│   └── conformance_spec/\n│       └── mod.rs          (stub)\n└── adapters/\n    ├── mod.rs\n    └── fs.rs               (filesystem adapter: workspace creation, config I/O, atomic writes, prompt hashing)\n```\n\n### Key Architectural Principles Implemented\n\n1. **Bounded Contexts:** Clean separation of concerns across six contexts (workspace governance, workflow composition, project/run record, agent execution, requirements drafting, automation runtime, conformance spec)\n2. **Domain-Driven Design:** Core domain types in `shared/domain.rs` used throughout\n3. **Ports & Adapters:** Service layers define ports; filesystem adapter implements them\n4. **Fail-Fast:** Workspace version checking, validation before mutations, corrupt-record detection\n5. **Atomic Operations:** Project creation, config writes use temp-then-rename pattern\n6. **Durable History vs Runtime Logs:** Strict separation—journal + payloads/artifacts never mixed with runtime logs\n7. **Deterministic Rendering:** Markdown artifacts from validated structured payloads only\n8. **Flow Immutability:** Once a project is created with a flow, the flow cannot be changed\n\n### Contexts Still to Implement (Future Loops)\n\n1. **Agent Execution** - Agent-driven stage execution with structured-output guarantee\n2. **Requirements Drafting** - Requirements intake and transformation\n3. **Automation Runtime** - Workflow orchestration and lifecycle management\n\nThese will build on the foundation (loops 1-4) to complete the full ralph-burning rewrite delivery roadmap."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: afc58c77e2b5589b8 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 42358\ntool_uses: 17\nduration_ms: 37534</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"68f65612-956d-4383-9b3f-2ff2c684a050","uuid":"f4ecb762-7f1d-4f96-bd36-fecee5857097","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read all the 