{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015umV9Ff8rGC1wuGDkBQWvr","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me provide a comprehensive exploration report.\n\n## Complete Code Exploration Report: ralph-burning-rewrite\n\nI've thoroughly explored the ralph-burning-rewrite codebase (32 Rust source files). Here's what's currently implemented:\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── main.rs                          # Entry point with async tokio runtime\n├── lib.rs                           # Library root (exports: adapters, cli, contexts, shared)\n├── shared/\n│   ├── domain.rs                    # Core domain types\n│   └── error.rs                     # Error types (AppError, ContractError)\n├── cli/\n│   ├── mod.rs                       # CLI dispatcher (8 subcommands)\n│   ├── init.rs                      # Workspace initialization\n│   ├── config.rs                    # Config show/get/set/edit\n│   ├── flow.rs                      # Flow list/show\n│   ├── project.rs                   # Project create/select/list/show/delete\n│   ├── run.rs                       # Run status/history/tail (start/resume/rollback stubbed)\n│   ├── requirements.rs              # Requirements (all stubbed)\n│   ├── daemon.rs                    # Daemon (all stubbed)\n│   └── conformance.rs               # Conformance testing (all stubbed)\n├── adapters/\n│   ├── mod.rs\n│   └── fs.rs                        # Filesystem adapter implementations\n├── contexts/\n│   ├── mod.rs\n│   ├── workspace_governance/        # Workspace init & config management\n│   │   ├── mod.rs                   # Core initialization logic\n│   │   └── config.rs                # EffectiveConfig with TOML parsing\n│   ├── project_run_record/          # Project & run state management\n│   │   ├── mod.rs                   # Context name & re-exports\n│   │   ├── model.rs                 # All data models (ProjectRecord, RunSnapshot, etc.)\n│   │   ├── service.rs               # Ports & use cases (create, list, show, delete, run queries)\n│   │   ├── journal.rs               # Journal event parsing\n│   │   └── queries.rs               # Run status/history/tail query implementations\n│   ├── workflow_composition/        # Flow definitions & stage contracts\n│   │   ├── mod.rs                   # FlowDefinition + 4 built-in flows\n│   │   ├── contracts.rs             # Stage contract registry & evaluation\n│   │   ├── payloads.rs              # Typed stage payloads (Planning/Execution/Validation)\n│   │   └── renderers.rs             # Markdown artifact rendering\n│   ├── requirements_drafting/       # Placeholder (CONTEXT_NAME only)\n│   ├── agent_execution/             # Placeholder (CONTEXT_NAME only)\n│   ├── conformance_spec/            # Placeholder (CONTEXT_NAME only)\n│   └── automation_runtime/          # Placeholder (CONTEXT_NAME only)\n└── tests/\n    ├── unit/\n    │   ├── domain_test.rs\n    │   ├── flow_preset_test.rs\n    │   ├── config_test.rs\n    │   ├── workspace_test.rs\n    │   ├── active_project_test.rs\n    │   ├── project_run_record_test.rs\n    │   ├── adapter_contract_test.rs\n    │   ├── stage_contract_test.rs\n    │   ├── renderer_test.rs\n    │   ├── journal_test.rs\n    │   └── query_test.rs\n    ├── unit.rs                      # Test aggregator\n    └── cli.rs                        # CLI integration tests\n```\n\n### CLI Commands (Wired Up)\n\n**Fully Implemented:**\n- `ralph-burning init` - Initialize workspace\n- `ralph-burning config show|get|set|edit` - Manage workspace configuration\n- `ralph-burning flow list|show` - Display flow definitions\n- `ralph-burning project create|select|list|show|delete` - Project lifecycle\n- `ralph-burning run status|history|tail` - Query run state and history\n\n**Stubbed (return NotYetImplemented):**\n- `ralph-burning run start|resume|rollback` - Run execution\n- `ralph-burning requirements draft|quick|show|answer` - Requirements generation\n- `ralph-burning daemon start|status|abort|retry|reconcile` - Background service\n- `ralph-burning conformance list|run` - Conformance testing\n\n### Domain Types (shared/domain.rs)\n\n**Enums:**\n- `FlowPreset` - 4 variants: Standard, QuickDev, DocsChange, CiImprovement\n- `StageId` - 16 variants (PromptReview, Planning, Implementation, Qa, Review, CompletionPanel, AcceptanceQa, FinalReview, PlanAndImplement, ApplyFixes, DocsPlan, DocsUpdate, DocsValidation, CiPlan, CiUpdate, CiValidation)\n- `FailureClass` - 6 variants for retry semantics (TransportFailure, SchemaValidationFailure, DomainValidationFailure, Timeout, Cancellation, QaReviewOutcomeFailure)\n\n**Structs:**\n- `StageCursor` - Track stage progression (stage, cycle, attempt, completion_round)\n- `ProjectId` - Validated project identifier\n- `RunId` - Validated run identifier\n- `WorkspaceConfig` - Workspace metadata with version and settings\n- `WorkspaceSettings` - Configuration (prompt_review, default_flow, default_backend, default_model)\n- `PromptReviewSettings` - Enable/disable prompt review\n\n**Constants:**\n- `CURRENT_WORKSPACE_VERSION = 1`\n\n### Data Models (project_run_record/model.rs)\n\n**Project State:**\n- `ProjectRecord` - Immutable metadata (id, name, flow, prompt_reference, prompt_hash, created_at, status_summary)\n- `ProjectStatusSummary` - Created, Active, Completed, Failed\n\n**Run State:**\n- `RunSnapshot` - Canonical run progression (active_run, status, cycle_history, completion_rounds, rollback_point_meta, amendment_queue)\n- `ActiveRun` - Current stage cursor and start time\n- `RunStatus` - NotStarted, Running, Paused, Completed, Failed\n- `CycleHistoryEntry` - Track cycle progression\n\n**Journal & Events:**\n- `JournalEvent` - Immutable event log (sequence, timestamp, event_type, details)\n- `JournalEventType` - ProjectCreated, RunStarted, StageEntered, StageCompleted, CycleAdvanced, CompletionRoundAdvanced, RunCompleted, RunFailed, RollbackCreated, AmendmentQueued\n\n**History & Logs:**\n- `PayloadRecord` - Durable stage payloads (payload_id, stage_id, cycle, attempt, created_at, payload)\n- `ArtifactRecord` - Rendered outputs (artifact_id, payload_id, stage_id, created_at, content)\n- `RuntimeLogEntry` - Timestamped logs (timestamp, level, source, message)\n- `RollbackPoint` - Snapshot for rollback (rollback_id, created_at, stage_id, cycle, run_snapshot)\n- `SessionStore` - Session metadata (for future use, currently empty)\n\n**Views:**\n- `ProjectListEntry` - For `project list` output\n- `ProjectDetail` - For `project show` output\n\n### Services & Ports (project_run_record/service.rs)\n\n**Port Interfaces (trait contracts):**\n- `ProjectStorePort` - CRUD for project records, atomic creation, staged deletion\n- `JournalStorePort` - Read journal, append events\n- `ArtifactStorePort` - List payloads and artifacts\n- `RuntimeLogStorePort` - Read runtime logs\n- `RunSnapshotPort` - Read run state\n- `ActiveProjectPort` - Manage active project pointer\n\n**Use Cases:**\n- `create_project()` - Create with atomic initialization\n- `list_projects()` - With active project marking\n- `show_project()` - Detailed view\n- `delete_project()` - With run state validation\n- `run_status()` - Query current run state\n- `run_history()` - Journal-based history\n- `run_tail()` - Latest run status with optional logs\n\n### Filesystem Adapter (adapters/fs.rs)\n\n**Adapter Implementations:**\n- `FsProjectStore` - Implements ProjectStorePort\n- `FsJournalStore` - Implements JournalStorePort\n- `FsArtifactStore` - Implements ArtifactStorePort\n- `FsRuntimeLogStore` - Implements RuntimeLogStorePort\n- `FsRunSnapshotStore` - Implements RunSnapshotPort\n- `FsActiveProjectStore` - Implements ActiveProjectPort\n\n**Project Structure on Disk:**\n```\n.ralph-burning/\n├── workspace.toml\n├── active-project\n├── projects/\n│   └── {project-id}/\n│       ├── project.toml\n│       ├── prompt.md\n│       ├── run.json\n│       ├── journal.ndjson\n│       ├── sessions.json\n│       ├── history/\n│       │   ├── payloads/\n│       │   └── artifacts/\n│       ├── runtime/\n│       │   ├── logs/\n│       │   ├── backend/\n│       │   └── temp/\n│       ├── amendments/\n│       └── rollback/\n├── requirements/\n├── daemon/\n│   ├── tasks/\n│   └── leases/\n```\n\n### Workflow Composition (workflow_composition/)\n\n**Flow Definitions:**\n- **Standard** (8 stages): PromptReview → Planning → Implementation → Qa → Review → CompletionPanel → AcceptanceQa → FinalReview\n- **QuickDev** (4 stages): PlanAndImplement → Review → ApplyFixes → FinalReview\n- **DocsChange** (4 stages): DocsPlan → DocsUpdate → DocsValidation → Review\n- **CiImprovement** (4 stages): CiPlan → CiUpdate → CiValidation → Review\n\n**Stage Contracts (contracts.rs):**\n- Contract registry mapping each StageId to exactly one contract\n- Three payload families:\n  - **Planning**: prompt_review, planning, docs_plan, ci_plan\n  - **Execution**: implementation, plan_and_implement, apply_fixes, docs_update, ci_update\n  - **Validation**: qa, docs_validation, ci_validation, acceptance_qa, review, final_review, completion_panel\n\n**Typed Payloads (payloads.rs):**\n- `PlanningPayload` - problem_framing, assumptions_or_open_questions, proposed_work, readiness\n- `ExecutionPayload` - change_summary, steps, validation_evidence, outstanding_risks\n- `ValidationPayload` - outcome (Approved/ConditionallyApproved/RequestChanges/Rejected), evidence, findings_or_gaps, follow_up_or_amendments\n- `ExecutionStep` - order, description, status (Intended/Completed/Skipped)\n- `ProposedWorkItem` - order, summary, details\n\n**Renderers (renderers.rs):**\n- Deterministic Markdown artifact generation from payloads\n\n### Workspace Governance (workspace_governance/)\n\n**Config Management (config.rs):**\n- `EffectiveConfig` - Compose workspace settings from workspace.toml\n- `ConfigEntry` - Key-value with source tracking\n- `ConfigValue` - Typed configuration values\n- Supported keys: prompt_review.enabled, default_flow, default_backend, default_model\n\n**Initialization:**\n- Version checking\n- Project existence validation\n- Active project resolution\n\n### Error Handling (shared/error.rs)\n\n**AppError variants:**\n- `AlreadyInitialized`, `WorkspaceConflict`, `InvalidStageCursorField`, `InvalidIdentifier`, `InvalidFlowPreset`\n- `UnsupportedWorkspaceVersion`, `UnknownConfigKey`, `InvalidConfigValue`\n- `NoActiveProject`, `ProjectNotFound`, `EditorFailed`, `DuplicateProject`\n- `CorruptRecord`, `InvalidPrompt`, `ActiveRunDelete`, `JournalSequence`\n- `NotYetImplemented` - For stubbed commands\n- IO/TOML/JSON passthrough errors\n\n**ContractError variants (for stage validation):**\n- `SchemaValidation`, `DomainValidation`, `RenderError`, `QaReviewOutcome`\n- Maps to FailureClass for retry policies\n\n### Tests (11 unit test files, 2 integration suites)\n\n- **domain_test.rs** - Domain type validation\n- **flow_preset_test.rs** - Flow definition tests\n- **config_test.rs** - Configuration parsing & validation\n- **workspace_test.rs** - Workspace initialization\n- **active_project_test.rs** - Active project management\n- **project_run_record_test.rs** - Project CRUD & run state\n- **adapter_contract_test.rs** - Filesystem adapter contracts\n- **stage_contract_test.rs** - Stage contract registry\n- **renderer_test.rs** - Markdown rendering\n- **journal_test.rs** - Journal event parsing\n- **query_test.rs** - Run status/history/tail queries\n- **unit.rs** - Unit test aggregator\n- **cli.rs** - CLI integration tests\n\n### Implementation Status Summary\n\n**Fully Implemented:**\n- Workspace initialization and configuration management\n- Project CRUD operations with atomic guarantees\n- Run state tracking with journal-based history\n- Filesystem persistence layer with all ports\n- Flow definitions and stage contract registry\n- Typed payload families and renderers\n- Query interfaces for run status/history/tail\n- Error handling with semantic validation\n\n**Stubbed/Placeholder:**\n- Run execution (start, resume, rollback)\n- Requirements drafting context\n- Agent execution context\n- Conformance testing\n- Automation runtime\n- Daemon service\n- Journal event serialization details (module exists but limited coverage)\n\n**Key Architectural Patterns:**\n1. **Hexagonal Architecture** - Ports define contracts, adapters implement them\n2. **Domain-Driven Design** - Strong typing with domain validation\n3. **Single Source of Truth** - run.json is canonical state, never inferred\n4. **Atomic Operations** - Project creation uses staging + rename pattern\n5. **Durable History** - Journal + payloads + artifacts separate from state\n6. **Deterministic Contracts** - Fixed schema validation → semantic validation → rendering\n\n**File Paths for Reference:**\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/mod.rs` - CLI dispatcher\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs` - Domain types\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs` - Port definitions\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs` - Filesystem implementations\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs` - Flow definitions\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs` - Stage contracts"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a13f0cc6f2e49740c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 58934\ntool_uses: 37\nduration_ms: 59660</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"68f65612-956d-4383-9b3f-2ff2c684a050","uuid":"156d1d0b-f802-4afa-abb8-f2b4ed4703a8","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the ralph-burning-rewrite/src/ directory to understand what code currently exists. Look at:\n1. The directory structure (all files under ralph-burning-rewrite/src/)\n2. Key module files (mod.rs